 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are given a piece of text describing an SVG path element and a multiple choice options list. Your task is to classify the described SVG path into one of the following categories, using only the letters: B, C, D, E, F, G, I, J, K.\n\nCategories are defined as follows:\n- B: heptagon (seven-sided polygon)\n- C: hexagon (six-sided polygon)\n- D: kite (quadrilateral with two distinct pairs of adjacent, congruent sides)\n- E: line (straight segment)\n- F: octagon (eight-sided polygon)\n- G: pentagon (five-sided polygon)\n- I: sector (portion of a circle bounded by two radii and the connecting arc)\n- J: triangle (three-sided polygon)\n- K: ellipse (ellipse shape, including circles—see note below)\n\nImportant details and domain-specific guidance:\n- The input text typically includes the SVG path's command string (the \"d\" attribute).\n- The assistant must analyze the SVG path data to infer which geometric shape is being described.\n- While the input may contain the full list of options (A-K or A-J), you should only respond using one of: B, C, D, E, F, G, I, J, K.\n- The option 'K' (ellipse) includes both ellipses and circles, even if 'A' (circle) is present in the choices.\n- Do not respond with 'A' (circle) under any circumstances; always use 'K' for a circle or ellipse.\n- Only reply with a single uppercase letter corresponding to the correct category.\n- No further explanation or commentary is required."
 },
